Playing off handicap 20, Malakwen posted an impressive 40 points, beating lady golfer Faith Chemutai, Dennis Flapan and Ben Chruiyot on countback.In fifth place was William Muguima who posted 38 points.  Despite bogeying a number of shots in a rather tough day, Catherine Gitonga still managed to beat lady winner Esther Wanjiku and Susan Kanyora on countback, to claim the overall title during Lady Captain’s (Edith Ngugi) tournament at the par 72 Ruiru Sports Club course at the weekend. 

Playing off handicap 23, Gitonga carded 17 in the first nine and 19 points at the back nine for a total of 36 points, same as Wanjiku, though Gitonga scored better at the last six holes. 



