Rosemary Mkok and her partner also on 41 points came home third, though also after a countback with the pair of Petty Kigwe and B.Kinyanjui. 

Agnes Wanjiru and L. Waweru were fifth on 40 points, which was one better than the pair of Eva Njukia and Louisa Gitau, who took the sixth prize on 39 points. 

The remaining three prizes were decided on countback with Dianne O’Connor and Phylis Kimbo taking the seventh prize as Grace Gakiria and M. Kimemia and Mary Maingi and Wanjiru Karume taking the eighth and ninth prizes respectively. 

The two nines went to Beatrice Soy and J. Kimondo on 20 points and Regina Gachora and W. Gitonga on 22 points. 

At Kitale Club, former club captain Stephen Malakwen Stephen Malakwen displayed awesome golfing skills to clinch the third leg of the NCBA Golf Series/ 

Playing off handicap 20, Malakwen posted an impressive 40 points, beating lady golfer Faith Chemutai, Dennis Flapan and Ben Chruiyot on countback. 

In fifth place was William Muguima who posted 38 points.  

The following are summarised weekend results; At Nakuru; Ngao Credit Golf Day; Overall winner- Gurviv Sagoo 41 (19, 22), Indraj Singh 40 cb Philip Gathii, Man winner- Dominic Walubengo 38, Lady winner- Linda Munyao, Guest winner- Javan Muriithi 37, Gross Winner- Paul Muhia 32, Nines: Teresia Muturi 23, Fredrick Mbuthia 21 pts. At Eldoret Golf Club: Syngenta Lumax Golf Day; Overall Winner- David Rotich 62 nett, Sahill Aggarwal 64 nett, Virginia Mutei 65 nett, cb Mercy Karonei, Elly Barno 67 nett, Nines; Kiptoo Koross 30 nett, Tom Mutei 31 nett. At Mombasa Golf Club; Chairman’s Prize (Ken Mwangi); Overall winner- Paul Munyao 41 pts, Men winner- Vincent Muriungi 39, Henry Kamau 38 cb Elvis Nduati 38, Best Lady- Carol Mokaya 35, Gladys Mutisya 32, Caroline Munyi 31, Best Junior- Mwai Mariga 32, Best Senior- Paul Macharia 23, Best Past Chairman- Elijah Ibua 36 pts. At Vet Lab: February Monthly Mug Sponsored by the Captain's Kitty; Overall Winner- Patrick Karimi 68 nett, Kish Joshi 69, cb Francis Musila 69, Lady winner- Channelle Wangari 70 nett, Rachel Ndei 71, Guest winner- Bethwell Ndungu 66 nett. 



